President Obama was briefed on the second case of Ebola in Dallas, Texas. He spoke with Secretary of Health and Human Services Sylvia Burwell, who updated him on the response to the diagnosis. The President directed the CDC to investigate the breach in infection control protocols at the Dallas hospital quickly. He also asked that additional CDC officers work with local authorities and hospital staff to review infection control procedures. The President wants the lessons learned from the inquiry to be shared widely. He also requested that federal authorities take immediate steps to ensure hospitals and healthcare providers nationwide are prepared to follow protocols if they encounter an Ebola patient. The President asked Secretary Burwell to continue updating him on the response.